<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-1393] TTransportException&apos;s thrown from THttpClient contain superfluous slashes in the Exception message</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-1393</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This is a very minor issue, but should be addressed nonetheless.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The THttpClient class ensures the $uri_ property has a slash prefixed by appending one if needed in the constructor. However in THttpClient::read, there are 2 exceptions thrown where a slash is concatenated between the port and uri. This results in a superfluous slash in the TTransportException message.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Example:&lt;br/&gt;
&quot;THttpClient: Could not read 184549154 bytes from xxx.yyy.com:80//randomService&quot;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
